FBIS4-53810 "dreas100aa_94004" FBIS-EAS-94-100 Daily Report 20 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Further on Proceedings at Singapore Conference Further on Proceedings at Singapore Conference SRV Planning Minister Speaks BK2205122694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 20 May 94 BK2205122694 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam English BFN [Text] Chairman of the Vietnamese State Planning Committee Do Quoc Sam said Vietnam needs about $50 billion in the next six years in order to develop its economy. This sum is expected from foreign aid and loans, with half used in services and building infrastructure. Only 12 percent will be allocated for agriculture and 38 percent for industrial development. He was addressing a conference in Singapore on trade opportunities for China, Vietnam, and ASEAN.
